section.p:
To avoid any downtime, before removing a replica (or index), first create an equivalent index for your queries to continue using.If you created an index on node 192.168.10.10 with replicas on nodes 192.168.10.11 and 192.168.10.12 and later decided you didn't want the 2nd replica, then you'll need to remove the index (which removes all replicas) and then re-create the index with only one replica.CREATE INDEX country_idx ON `travel-sample`(country, city) WHERE type="route" USING GSI WITH {"nodes":["192.168.10.10:8091", "192.168.10.11:8091", "192.168.10.12:8091"]};
DROP INDEX `travel-sample`.country_idx;
CREATE INDEX country_idx ON `travel-sample`(country, city) WHERE type="route" USING GSI WITH {"nodes":["192.168.10.10:8091", "192.168.10.11:8091"]};
